    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.29.45-46"/>
                <note type="curatorial">45</note>
                <fw type ="authorial">
                    THE UNIVERSITY OF NEBRASKA
                    LINCOLN 8, NEBRASKA
                    OFFICE OF DIRECTOR
                    UNIVERSITY OF NEBRASKA PRESS
                </fw>
                
                <dateline>February 21, 1961</dateline>
                
                <opener>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>John Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Skyrim, Route 7</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Columbia, Missouri</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>But coincidence, I was about to write you for copies of published reviews of Black Elk. I would appreciate getting some from some of the principal reviewing journals, from which we will make extracts. I'm not sure an unpublished thesis would fill our promotional needs for advertising and directing mail pieces. Your new introduction is of great help.</p>
                
                <closer>
                    <note type="authorial">UNIVERSITY OF NEBRASKA PRESS</note>
                    <signed>Bruce H. Nicoll</signed>
                    <signed>Bruce H. Nicoll</signed>
                    <note type="authorial">Director</note>
                </closer>
                
                <note type="authorial">BHN:mv</note>
            </div1>
            
            <div1 type="envelope">
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.29.45-46"/>
